               <note>
                  
                  <ab type="history">It was a historical region located on the Sudanese border, in the north of the province of <placeName ref="LOC6186Walqay"/>, 
                     limited at great extent by the <placeName ref="LOC5697Setit"/>and<placeName ref="LOC5864Takkaz"/> 
                     river, in what is today <placeName ref="LOC2991Eritre"/>. It was a region with hot and dry climate, a fortunate circumstance during 16th century for King 
                     <persName ref="PRS4428Galawdew"/> as while <placeName ref="Q2359535"/> fighting there suffered because of the harsh climatic condition. Prior to  the sixteenth century,
                     it was an Islamic Sultanate, inhabited by <persName ref="ETH1194Balaw"/> and ruled by  
                     <persName ref="PRS6537Makattar"/>, an ally of <persName ref="PRS1522Ahmadb"/>.  
                     <persName ref="PRS6537Makattar"/> died shortly after<persName ref="PRS1522Ahmadb"/>, the rule  was taken over by his own sister, 
                     <persName ref="PRS4406Gaewa"/>, who made alliance with the <placeName ref="Q2359535"/>. She was defeated in <date>1557</date>, 
                     and the region was finally incorporated in the Christian empire. </ab>     
               </note>
               
               
               
               
